<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideed13fd5-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s1598"><num value="1598">§ 1598.</num><heading> Notice of intention to prosecute</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Before any violation of this chapter is reported by the Secretary of Agriculture to any United States attorney for institution of a criminal proceeding, the person against whom such proceeding is contemplated shall be given appropriate notice and an opportunity to prevent <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002182">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002182"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be “present”.</note> his views, either orally or in writing, with regard to such contemplated proceeding.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ideed13fd6-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1939-08-09/ch615">Aug. 9, 1939, ch. 615</ref>, title IV, § 408, <ref href="/us/stat/53/1286">53 Stat. 1286</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
